   Hirohito is remembered for surrendering in WW II.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Though many world leaders mourned his passing,
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   South Korea and others viewed him as a symbol of Japanese crimes against Asian people.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Generally portrayed as a peaceful man, a January BBC documentary claims
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   that Truman decided not to prosecute Hirohito for war crimes,
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   and that Japan's wartime prime minister was pressured into changing his testimony
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   to avoid incriminating the emperor.
  </a>
